The paper focuses on developing a flexible and open-ended perception system for robot manipulation tasks, which suggests a strong emphasis on robotics (cs.RO). The system involves capturing parts of the point cloud from the demonstration scene, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for localizing landmarks in new scenes, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents findings from a user evaluation of the landmark specification interface, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
